title: American horror story coven - Queenie kills Madam delphine LaLaurie
author: ONCEUPON a HORRORSTORY
comment: "I don't wanna die" "Tough shit, who does?" Delphine got exactly what was coming to her foul ass!
I'm glad that LaLaurie was not redeemed, because someone that cruel and sadistic shouldn't get a second chance, she did so much evil things to people,  so Queenie could do what was right.

LaLaurie was a racist, sadistic, even psychopathic killer, but she made some relevant points in the end. Lots of people aren't sorry for what they do, they're sorry because people find out or they get caught, and even when they say the words deep down we know most people don't mean. But LaLaurie, she was honest about it, she wasn't repentant and saw no point in pretending to be. What does it tell you when the worst of humanity are more honest than everyone else?
I’m sorry but Delphine Lalaurie offered some true words on our society. Apologizing just because they’re sorry they got caught.
description:
American horror story coven - Queenie offers Madam Delphine LaLaurie a chance for redemption then kills her
3x12 Go to hell
